Subject: [RFC/POC PATCH] block: scaffold Kairo request classification

Local RFC/POC patch scaffold.

This patch sketches internal Kairo request classification helpers without
introducing a permanent UAPI.

Current local signaling method:
- RT prio 0 read  -> KAIRO_DECODE_READ
- RT prio 1 read  -> KAIRO_PREFETCH_READ
- BE prio 7 write -> KAIRO_PREFILL_WRITE
- discard         -> KAIRO_EVICT

diff --git a/include/linux/blk_types.h b/include/linux/blk_types.h
index 333333333333..444444444444 100644
--- a/include/linux/blk_types.h
+++ b/include/linux/blk_types.h
@@
+enum kairo_class {
+	KAIRO_NONE = 0,
+	KAIRO_DECODE_READ,
+	KAIRO_PREFETCH_READ,
+	KAIRO_PREFILL_WRITE,
+	KAIRO_EVICT,
+};
+
diff --git a/block/blk-mq.c b/block/blk-mq.c
index 555555555555..666666666666 100644
--- a/block/blk-mq.c
+++ b/block/blk-mq.c
@@
+/*
+ * TODO: add local helper plumbing so mq-deadline and future schedulers can
+ * derive kairo_class from request ioprio without designing a new UAPI.
+ */
